{
  "stem": "293.4",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We already finished it.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Not too much to say.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The period in Brinnlitz from November 1944 till May 8, at the night, 12 o'clock at night, 1945, was extremely interesting part of our life and our history over there.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We've heard, everybody of us, that how long Schindler is with us, will nothing happen to us.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The minute he was not absent, we were very uneasy until, as a point I give you a situation what him came in in the first weeks in January 1945.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Two cattle train with about 136 people from Golleschau-- this was a sub-camp-- sub-camp of Auschwitz came.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They were six nights, seven days locked up without the food, without opening the gate, and every camp refused to accept them.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They came early morning on Sunday to the Brinnlitz and Schindler was not there.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Mrs.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Schindler, who deserves a tremendous credit for saving the lives of those people, that meant that cattle train should be open, and the people should be taken out because factory need much more worker because we're producing extremely important artillery shell for the army, and we have to deliver this.",
      "word_count": 50
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "We never produce anything.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Everything was faked.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And anything he needed to deliver he was buying on the black market, Mr.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Schindler, from another manufacturer, who were making the same shell.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Our shells were so bad that the ones we delivered, they start investigating why-- why they are so bad.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "But Schindler was not there.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And the Leipold, the-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Sturmfuhrer Leipold, who was in charge of the SS, about 40 of them, but they were elderly.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "The young, already, they were sent to the front.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "They were, like, in 40s and 50s, didn't want to keep this.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
